From: Jiri Bohac <jbohac@suse.cz>
Subject: kABI fix update for alarm_forward
Patch-mainline: Never, kABI fix
References: bsc#1214298

Related: bsc#1099922

Updates the kABI workaround patches.kabi/posix-timers-overrun-change-kABI-fix.patch
to the change introduced by patches.fixes/alarmtimers-add-alarm_forward-functionality.patch,
which adds another place where the overrun is modified, so we also need 
to update 32bit shadow copy.

---
 kernel/time/alarmtimer.c |    4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/kernel/time/alarmtimer.c
+++ b/kernel/time/alarmtimer.c
@@ -417,7 +417,9 @@ static enum alarmtimer_restart alarm_han
 
 	/* Re-add periodic timers */
 	if (alarm->period.tv64) {
-		ptr->it_overrun += alarm_forward(alarm, now, alarm->period);
+		u64 overrun = alarm_forward(alarm, now, alarm->period);
+		ptr->it_overrun += overrun;
+		ptr->__it_overrun += overrun;
 		result = ALARMTIMER_RESTART;
 	}
 	spin_unlock_irqrestore(&ptr->it_lock, flags);
